<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://elearning.trree.org">TRREE-for Africa</a> provides a multilingual, free access and free training program on research ethics and regulation with a focus on Sub-Saharian African countries.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.fhi.org/training/en/Retc/">Research Ethics Training Curriculum</a> has been prepared, by <a href="/wiki/Family_Health_International" title="Family Health International">Family Health International</a> (FHI), with a focus on <a href="/wiki/Human_experimentation" title="Human experimentation" class="mw-redirect">human experimentation</a>.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www1.umn.edu/ships/ethics/research.htm">Research Ethics</a> section of the SHiPS (<b>S</b>ociology, <b>Hi</b>story and <b>P</b>hilosophy of <b>S</b>cience) website provides some useful resources, including case studies relevant to <a href="/wiki/Scientific_misconduct" title="Scientific misconduct">scientific misconduct</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.sgr.org.uk">Scientists for Global Responsibility (UK)</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.inesglobal.com">INES Global</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.pre.ethics.gc.ca/eng/policy-politique/initiatives/tcps2-eptc2/Default/">The Tri-Council Policy Statement (Canada)</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.unesco.org/ethics">UNESCO - Ethics of Science and Technology</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.lfcc.on.ca/ethical.html">Ethical Practice: Principles and Guidelines for Research with Vulnerable Individuals and Families</a> An ethical protocol for social science research developed by the Centre for Children and Families in the Justice System</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.hinxtongroup.org">The Hinxton Group: An International Consortium on Stem Cells, Ethics &amp; Law</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.bioethicsinstitute.org/web/page/657/sectionid/377/pagelevel/3/interior.asp">Johns Hopkins Program in Research Ethics</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://ahp.yorku.ca/?p=80">Bibliography</a> of peer-reviewed journal articles on the history of the use of deception in research, as well as on the histories of experimental ethics.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://icmr.nic.in/ethical.pdf">https://icmr.nic.in/ethical.pdf</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://www.researchethics.ca">https://www.researchethics.ca</a> ResearchEthics.ca</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://www.researchethicsblog.com">https://www.researchethicsblog.com</a> The Research Ethics Blog</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://www.asanet.org/cs/root/leftnav/ethics/cope_policies_and_procedures">https://www.asanet.org/cs/root/leftnav/ethics/cope_policies_and_procedures</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://www.aaanet.org/committees/ethics/ethcode.htm">https://www.aaanet.org/committees/ethics/ethcode.htm</a></li>
</ul>
